<div class="quiz-box">
<div class="quiz-question">What are the five stages of death according to Kubler-Ross?</div>

<div class="quiz-option"
     data-wrong="This sequence is not part of Kubler-Ross' model and omits key emotional processes such as bargaining and depression."
     onclick="showFeedback(this, false, 'quiz1')">
Shock, denial, anger, acceptance, resolution
</div>

<div class="quiz-option"
     data-correct="Denial, anger, bargaining, depression, and acceptance"
     onclick="showFeedback(this, true, 'quiz1')">
Denial, anger, bargaining, depression, and acceptance
</div>

<div class="quiz-option"
     data-wrong="Although these terms appear in the theory, the order is incorrect and does not reflect the accepted progression."
     onclick="showFeedback(this, false, 'quiz1')">
Bargaining, denial, acceptance, anger, and depression
</div>

<div class="quiz-option"
     data-wrong="These terms are not part of the established Kubler-Ross stages."
     onclick="showFeedback(this, false, 'quiz1')">
Resistance, denial, grief, anger, and acceptance
</div>

<div id="quiz1-feedback"
     class="quiz-feedback"
     data-rationale="Kubler-Ross' theory outlines a psychological process individuals go through when facing terminal illness or significant grief; the stages represent a common, though non-linear, emotional journey.">
</div>
</div>

